  "text": "Markov Decision Problems We consider the problem of undiscounted episodic reinforcement learning (RL) [CITATION_1] , where an RL agent interacts with a stochastic environment and this interaction is modeled as a discrete-time MDP. An MDP is a quintuple S, A, P, R, H , where S and A are the set of states and actions, P is the state transition distribution, The function R : S × A → ℜ is a real-valued function on the state-action space and the horizon H is the length of episode. We denote by P (·|x, a) and R(x, a) the probability distribution over the next state and the immediate reward of taking action a at state x, respectively. The agent interacts with the environment in a sequence of episodes. The interaction between the agent and environment at every episode 2 k ∈ [K] is as follows: starting from x k,1 ∈ S which is chosen by the environment, the agent interacts with the environment for H steps by following a sequence of actions chosen in A and observes a sequence of next-states and rewards until the end of episode. The initial state x k,1 may change arbitrarily from one episode to the next. We also use the notation · 1 for the ℓ 1 norm throughout this paper.",
